I still do not fully get why dairy specifically is so good at buffering toxicity. A friend said welders at his job got the metallic taste out of their mouths by drinking milk. In Bulgaria they gave free yogurt to factory workers exposed to industrial chemicals. How does it do it?
Reading Jack Vance novelettes and wondering if him and L. Ron Hubbard knew each other and if so what they thought of the other.

Fun fact, but Gene Wolfe used to take St. John's wort for his PTSD nightmares after coming home from the Korean War. Its main compound is Hypericin, a red oil described by Dr. Ray Peat as a "large system of conjugated electrons". Red compounds are generally antioxidants too.
There are a lot of anecdotes about Cyproheptadine helping with chronic nightmares even though at dosages above like 1 mg it tends to produce very vivid and bizarre dreams.
